  "body": "### Description\r\nA new account is created when trying to recover an account with invalid passphrase and password. when you log in the account it does not seems that account existed before.\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAn error message stating the the account does not exist should be displayed\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nA new account is created when trying to recover an account with invalid passphrase and password.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Select \"Recover access\", the \"Recover access\" page is displayed.\r\n- Tap the space bar 15 times on the \"Passphrase\" field.\r\n- Tap the space bar 15 times on the \"Password\" field, the \"Recover Access\" button is activated.\r\n- Tap the Recover Access\" button,  the \"Recover access\"  disappears, the \"Sign in status\" page is displayed again and an account is added to the page.\r\n- Log in the account using the prevuois password, it seems like a new account has been created instead of recovering an existing one.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: Nightly build: 0.9.10-432-g2bd7652b+\r\nSamsung Galaxy S6 & iPhone SE\r\n* Operating System: <Android> Android version: 6.0.1 &  IOS version: 11.1.2\r\n",
